answers.body_markdown:
This is an sql-server query. You may need to change `datediff` to an appropriate function of your DBMS. I assume you need the latest (as your desired output `2017-10-1 05:03` shows) row having a previous row within 3 minutes for a given id.

    select id, name, dt 
    from (
      select id, name, dt, row_number() over(partition by id order by dt desc) rn
      from (
        select id, name, dt
          , datediff(minute, lag(dt) over(partition by id order by dt), dt) diff
        from people 
      ) p
      where diff &lt;= 3
    ) p
    where rn=1;

